          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":2,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":55,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":339,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":339,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":55,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":339,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Keep effort genuinely conversational — you should be able to speak in full sentences throughout. Stay in the 5:07–5:39/km range and let feel guide you within that window.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Start with 5 minutes of brisk walking and dynamic leg swings before easing into your easy pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with 5 minutes of easy walking and light calf and hip flexor stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run is pure aerobic base work — its job is to add volume without adding stress. After a solid long run on Sunday, Tuesday's easy run helps flush fatigue and reinforces your aerobic engine. Resist the urge to push the pace here; the adaptation happens during recovery, not during the effort itself.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"title\":\"VO2Max Intervals\",\"target_distance_km\":14,\"target_duration_minutes\":60,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":339,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":237,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":339,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy, relaxed jogging. Let your body gradually wake up — no surges or strides yet.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":30,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":237,\"intensity\":\"VO2Max\",\"repetitions\":6,\"notes\":\"6 × 1 km at 3:57/km with 90-second easy jog recovery between reps. Each rep should feel hard but controlled — you're working, not sprinting. If rep 5 or 6 feels significantly harder than rep 1, slow slightly rather than blowing up.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":359,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow, easy jog back to full recovery. This is not optional — it's part of the workout.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog, finishing with 4 × 20-second strides at roughly 10K effort with full recovery between each.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog followed by dynamic stretching — leg swings, hip circles, and light quad and hamstring work.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"VO2max intervals are the sharpest tool in your kit for raising your aerobic ceiling. At VDOT 49.7, your 3:57/km interval pace is the right stimulus. For a 3:15 marathon, you need a strong aerobic ceiling — these sessions build it. The 90-second recovery keeps the quality honest without turning this into a sprint session. You've been handling 6 × 1 km well based on your recent history, so this is a continuation of that stimulus.\",\"perceived_effort\":8},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Threshold Cruise Intervals\",\"target_distance_km\":13,\"target_duration_minutes\":58,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":339,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":256,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":339,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog, relaxed breathing, no effort. Let your legs loosen up gradually.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":28,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":256,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":2,\"notes\":\"2 × 14 minutes at threshold pace (4:16/km) with 2 minutes easy jog between. Threshold effort should feel 'comfortably hard' — you could say a few words but not hold a conversation. If you drift faster than 4:10/km, ease back.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":359,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to bring heart rate down gradually. No rushing this.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog. You might add 2–3 short accelerations in the final few minutes to prime your legs for threshold effort.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog followed by 5 minutes of walking and static stretching — focus on calves, hamstrings, and hip flexors.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Threshold work is the cornerstone of marathon preparation. Running at lactate threshold teaches your body to clear lactate more efficiently, which directly translates to being able to hold marathon pace for 42 km. Cruise intervals (broken threshold rather than one continuous block) let you accumulate more quality time at threshold with slightly less accumulated fatigue than a single long tempo run — a smart trade-off given your 4-day schedule.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Aerobic Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":27,\"target_duration_minutes\":153,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":339,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":339,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":153,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":339,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Run the full distance at easy pace (5:07–5:39/km). The goal is time on feet and aerobic development — not pace. If you feel good in the final 5 km, you may naturally drift toward the faster end of easy, but do not push.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Start with 5 minutes of walking and dynamic movement before settling into your long run pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with 5–10 minutes of walking, then prioritize nutrition and hydration within 30 minutes. Light stretching once your heart rate has settled.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Your long run is the anchor of your marathon build. At 27 km this week (a modest step up from your recent 26 km), you're building the aerobic infrastructure — mitochondrial density, fat oxidation, and musculoskeletal resilience — that makes 42 km possible. The pace should feel easy enough that you could hold a conversation the entire way. Fueling practice is important here: aim to take in carbohydrates every 45 minutes to simulate race-day nutrition strategy.\",\"perceived_effort\":6}]}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
